This paper discusses the properties of groups in the context of collaborative search systems, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also proposes ways in which understanding group properties could influence the design of interfaces and algorithms, which falls under social and information sciences (cs.SI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and computers and society (cs.CY).
